'''Sangu Shrine''' (山宮神社, *Sangu Jinja*) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located at Shichikama, Shin'onsen, Mikata District, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|12=draft}}. It was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|12=draft}}. The main deity enshrined is {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|12=draft}}, with additional enshrinements of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|12=draft}}, {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|12=draft}}, {{ill|Homuda Wake no Mikoto|ja|誉田別尊|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|12=draft}}.
== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|12=draft}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In {{ill|1868|ja|1868th year|12=draft}} (the first year of the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|12=draft}}), it was renamed to its current title. In {{ill|1873|ja|1873rd year|12=draft}} (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|12=draft}} and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|12=draft}}.
The shrine's main hall was rebuilt in {{ill|1444|ja|1444th year|12=draft}} (Bun'an 1, {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代|12=draft}}), but was destroyed in {{ill|1944|ja|1944th year|12=draft}} (Shōwa 19) due to a typhoon. The current structure was rebuilt after World War II.
== Festivals and Events == * Annual Festival: September 29<ref>{{Cite web|title=Festival Calendar - Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.kirinnomachi-japan-heritage.jp/jp/reisai/1059/|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs}}</ref>
== Cultural Properties == * '''Shichikama {{ill|Kirin Shishi-mai|ja|麒麟獅子舞|12=draft}} Dance''' - Town-designated Intangible Folk Cultural Property (designated March 31, 1986)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Shichikama Kirin Shishi-mai|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=8ab359199e3f3c495d46db6ceb3791ec|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref> * '''Sangu Shrine Sacred Forest''' (山宮神社社叢) - Town-designated Natural Monument (designated March 31, 1986), featuring ancient {{ill|Castanopsis|ja|スダジイ|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hinoki cypress|ja|ヒノキ|12=draft}} trees, along with thick growths of {{ill|Camellia japonica|ja|ヤブツバキ|12=draft}} and {{ill|Sakaki|ja|サカキ|12=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sacred Forest of Shichikama Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=b500773414376fa6bd4970ec294860e2|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref>
== Access == * {{ill|West Japan Railway Company|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|12=draft}} (JR West) {{ill|San'in Main Line|ja|山陰本線|12=draft}}: From {{ill|Hamasaka Station|ja|浜坂駅|12=draft}}, take the {{ill|Zentan Bus|ja|全但バス|12=draft}} bound for {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|ja|湯村温泉|12=draft}}, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi" bus stop. 5-minute walk. * From Osaka or Kobe, take the Zentan Bus {{ill|Yumechiyo-go|ja|夢千代号|12=draft}} to "Yumura Onsen," transfer to the bus for Hamasaka, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi." 5-minute walk.
== Nearby Attractions == * {{ill|Hamasaka Onsenkyō|ja|浜坂温泉郷|12=draft}} ** {{ill|Hamasaka Onsen|ja|浜坂温泉|12=draft}} (9-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|ja|湯村温泉|12=draft}} (15-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Hamasaka Prefectural Sun Beach|ja|浜坂県民サンビーチ|12=draft}} * {{ill|Tajima Mihonoura|ja|但馬御火浦|12=draft}}
