'''Sangu Shrine''' (山宮神社, *Sangu Jinja*) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} located at Shichikama, Shin'onsen, Mikata District, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|12=draft|12=draft}}. The main deity enshrined is {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|12=draft|12=draft}}, with additional enshrinements of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Homuda Wake no Mikoto|ja|誉田別尊|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In {{ill|1868|ja|1868th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (the first year of the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft|12=draft}}), it was renamed to its current title. In {{ill|1873|ja|1873rd year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|12=draft|12=draft}} and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|12=draft|12=draft}}.
