{{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | Name = Sangu Shrine | image = [[File:Sangu-jinja Shinonsen03s5s4592.jpg|300px]] | location = {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Mikata District, Hyōgo|ja|美方郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Shin'onsen|ja|新温泉町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Shichikama 1409 | coordinates = {{coord|35|36|39.6|N|134|28|44.7|E|region:JP-28_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | deity = {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Type = Village Shrine (Former) | Established = Unknown | Main Hall = | Alternate Name = | Annual Festival = September 29 | Rituals = | Map = {{location map|Japan Hyogo|lat_deg=35|lat_min=36|lat_sec=39.6|lon_deg=134|lon_min=28|lon_sec=44.7|label=Sangu Shrine|position=center|width=200|float=center}} }}
'''Sangu Shrine''' (山宮神社, *Sangu Jinja*) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located at Shichikama, Shin'onsen, Mikata District, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The main deity enshrined is {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, with additional enshrinements of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Homuda Wake no Mikoto|ja|誉田別尊|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In {{ill|1868|ja|1868th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (the first year of the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), it was renamed to its current title. In {{ill|1873|ja|1873rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
The shrine's main hall was rebuilt in {{ill|1444|ja|1444th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Bun'an 1, {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), but was destroyed in {{ill|1944|ja|1944th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Shōwa 19) due to a typhoon. The current structure was rebuilt after World War II.
== Festivals and Events == * Annual Festival: September 29<ref>{{Cite web|title=Festival Calendar - Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.kirinnomachi-japan-heritage.jp/jp/reisai/1059/|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs}}</ref>
== Cultural Properties == * '''Shichikama {{ill|Kirin Shishi-mai|ja|麒麟獅子舞|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Dance''' - Town-designated Intangible Folk Cultural Property (designated March 31, 1986)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Shichikama Kirin Shishi-mai|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=8ab359199e3f3c495d46db6ceb3791ec|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref> * '''Sangu Shrine Sacred Forest''' (山宮神社社叢) - Town-designated Natural Monument (designated March 31, 1986), featuring ancient {{ill|Castanopsis|ja|スダジイ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Hinoki cypress|ja|ヒノキ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} trees, along with thick growths of {{ill|Camellia japonica|ja|ヤブツバキ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Sakaki|ja|サカキ|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sacred Forest of Shichikama Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=b500773414376fa6bd4970ec294860e2|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref>
== Access == * {{ill|West Japan Railway Company|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (JR West) {{ill|San'in Main Line|ja|山陰本線|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: From {{ill|Hamasaka Station|ja|浜坂駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, take the {{ill|Zentan Bus|ja|全但バス|qq=draft|qq=draft}} bound for {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyogo)|ja|湯村温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi" bus stop. 5-minute walk. * From Osaka or Kobe, take the Zentan Bus {{ill|Yumechiyo-go|ja|夢千代号|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to "Yumura Onsen," transfer to the bus for Hamasaka, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi." 5-minute walk.
== Nearby Attractions == * {{ill|Hamasaka Onsenkyō|ja|浜坂温泉郷|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ** {{ill|Hamasaka Onsen|ja|浜坂温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (9-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyogo)|ja|湯村温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (15-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Hamasaka Prefectural Sun Beach|ja|浜坂県民サンビーチ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Tajima Mihonoura|ja|但馬御火浦|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
