'''Sangu Shrine''' (山宮神社, *Sangu Jinja*) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located at Shichikama, Shin'onsen, Mikata District, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}}. It was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village shrine|qq=}}. The main deity enshrined is {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=}}, with additional enshrinements of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanagi|qq=}}, {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanami|qq=}}, {{ill|Homuda Wake no Mikoto|ja|誉田別尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Homuda Wake no Mikoto|qq=}}, and {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}}.
== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichikama Onsen|qq=}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In {{ill|1868|ja|1868th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1868|qq=}} (the first year of the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}}), it was renamed to its current title. In {{ill|1873|ja|1873rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1873|qq=}} (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman|qq=}} and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Placenta deity|qq=}}.
