'''Sangu Shrine''' (山宮神社, *Sangu Jinja*) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located at Shichikama, Shin'onsen, Mikata District, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}}. It was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village shrine|qq=}}. The main deity enshrined is {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=}}, with additional enshrinements of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanagi|qq=}}, {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanami|qq=}}, {{ill|Homuda Wake no Mikoto|ja|誉田別尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Homuda Wake no Mikoto|qq=}}, and {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}}.
== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichikama Onsen|qq=}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In {{ill|1868|ja|1868th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1868|qq=}} (the first year of the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}}), it was renamed to its current title. In {{ill|1873|ja|1873rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1873|qq=}} (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman|qq=}} and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Placenta deity|qq=}}.
The shrine's main hall was rebuilt in {{ill|1444|ja|1444th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1444|qq=}} (Bun'an 1, {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Muromachi period|qq=}}), but was destroyed in {{ill|1944|ja|1944th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1944|qq=}} (Shōwa 19) due to a typhoon. The current structure was rebuilt after World War II.
== Festivals and Events == * Annual Festival: September 29<ref>{{Cite web|title=Festival Calendar - Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.kirinnomachi-japan-heritage.jp/jp/reisai/1059/|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs}}</ref>
== Cultural Properties == * '''Shichikama {{ill|Kirin Shishi-mai|ja|麒麟獅子舞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kirin Shishi-mai|qq=}} Dance''' - Town-designated Intangible Folk Cultural Property (designated March 31, 1986)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Shichikama Kirin Shishi-mai|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=8ab359199e3f3c495d46db6ceb3791ec|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref> * '''Sangu Shrine Sacred Forest''' (山宮神社社叢) - Town-designated Natural Monument (designated March 31, 1986), featuring ancient {{ill|Castanopsis|ja|スダジイ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Castanopsis|qq=}} and {{ill|Hinoki cypress|ja|ヒノキ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoki cypress|qq=}} trees, along with thick growths of {{ill|Camellia japonica|ja|ヤブツバキ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Camellia japonica|qq=}} and {{ill|Sakaki|ja|サカキ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakaki|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sacred Forest of Shichikama Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=b500773414376fa6bd4970ec294860e2|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref>
== Access == * {{ill|West Japan Railway Company|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/West Japan Railway Company|qq=}} (JR West) {{ill|San'in Main Line|ja|山陰本線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/San'in Main Line|qq=}}: From {{ill|Hamasaka Station|ja|浜坂駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamasaka Station|qq=}}, take the {{ill|Zentan Bus|ja|全但バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zentan Bus|qq=}} bound for {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|ja|湯村温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|qq=}}, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi" bus stop. 5-minute walk. * From Osaka or Kobe, take the Zentan Bus {{ill|Yumechiyo-go|ja|夢千代号|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumechiyo-go|qq=}} to "Yumura Onsen," transfer to the bus for Hamasaka, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi." 5-minute walk.
== Nearby Attractions == * {{ill|Hamasaka Onsenkyō|ja|浜坂温泉郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamasaka Onsenkyō|qq=}} ** {{ill|Hamasaka Onsen|ja|浜坂温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamasaka Onsen|qq=}} (9-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|ja|湯村温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|qq=}} (15-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Hamasaka Prefectural Sun Beach|ja|浜坂県民サンビーチ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamasaka Prefectural Sun Beach|qq=}} * {{ill|Tajima Mihonoura|ja|但馬御火浦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tajima Mihonoura|qq=}}
