The shrine's main hall was rebuilt in [[:en:1444|1444]] (Bun'an 1, [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]]), but was destroyed in [[:en:1944|1944]] (Shōwa 19) due to a typhoon. The current structure was rebuilt after World War II.
== Festivals and Events == * Annual Festival: September 29<ref>{{Cite web|title=Festival Calendar - Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.kirinnomachi-japan-heritage.jp/jp/reisai/1059/|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs}}</ref>
== Cultural Properties == * '''Shichikama {{ill|Kirin Shishi-mai|ja|麒麟獅子舞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kirin Shishi-mai|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=麒麟獅子}} Dance''' - Town-designated Intangible Folk Cultural Property (designated March 31, 1986)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Shichikama Kirin Shishi-mai|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=8ab359199e3f3c495d46db6ceb3791ec|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref> * '''Sangu Shrine Sacred Forest''' (山宮神社社叢) - Town-designated Natural Monument (designated March 31, 1986), featuring ancient [[:en:Castanopsis sieboldii|Castanopsis]] and [[:en:Chamaecyparis obtusa|Hinoki cypress]] trees, along with thick growths of {{ill|Camellia japonica|ja|ヤブツバキ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Camellia japonica|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=ツバキ}} and [[:en:Cleyera japonica|Sakaki]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sacred Forest of Shichikama Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=b500773414376fa6bd4970ec294860e2|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref>
== Access == * [[:en:West Japan Railway Company|West Japan Railway Company]] (JR West) [[:en:San'in Main Line|San'in Main Line]]: From [[:en:Hamasaka Station|Hamasaka Station]], take the {{ill|Zentan Bus|ja|全但バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zentan Bus|qq=}} bound for {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|ja|湯村温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|qq=}}, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi" bus stop. 5-minute walk. * From Osaka or Kobe, take the Zentan Bus {{ill|Yumechiyo-go|ja|夢千代号|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumechiyo-go|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=全但バス}} to "Yumura Onsen," transfer to the bus for Hamasaka, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi." 5-minute walk.
== Nearby Attractions == * {{ill|Hamasaka Onsenkyō|ja|浜坂温泉郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamasaka Onsenkyō|qq=}} ** {{ill|Hamasaka Onsen|ja|浜坂温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamasaka Onsen|qq=}} (9-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|ja|湯村温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|qq=}} (15-minute bus ride) * {{ill|Hamasaka Prefectural Sun Beach|ja|浜坂県民サンビーチ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamasaka Prefectural Sun Beach|qq=}} * {{ill|Tajima Mihonoura|ja|但馬御火浦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tajima Mihonoura|qq=}}
