{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[Category:Has wikidata]][[d:Q11467748]] Wikidata name: [[Category:Add wikidata]] [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 05:33, 12 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[Category:Add wikidata]] Wikidata name: [[Category:Add wikidata]] [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:25, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | Name = Sangu Shrine | image = [[File:Sangu-jinja Shinonsen03s5s4592.jpg|300px]] | location = [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]], [[:en:Mikata District, Hyōgo|Mikata District, Hyōgo]], [[:en:Shin'onsen, Hyōgo|Shin'onsen]], Shichikama 1409 | coordinates = {{coord|35|36|39.6|N|134|28|44.7|E|region:JP-28_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | deity = {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=オオヤマツミ}} | Type = Village Shrine (Former) | Established = Unknown | Main Hall = | Alternate Name = | Annual Festival = September 29 | Rituals = | Map = {{location map|Japan Hyōgo|lat_deg=35|lat_min=36|lat_sec=39.6|lon_deg=134|lon_min=28|lon_sec=44.7|label=Sangu Shrine|position=center|width=200|float=center}} }}
'''Sangu Shrine''' (山宮神社, *Sangu Jinja*) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located at Shichikama, Shin'onsen, Mikata District, [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]]. It was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|lt=Son-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village shrine|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}}. The main deity enshrined is {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=オオヤマツミ}}, with additional enshrinements of [[:en:Izanagi|Izanagi]], [[:en:Izanami|Izanami]], {{ill|Homuda Wake no Mikoto|ja|誉田別尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Homuda Wake no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=応神天皇|1=Ōjin|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q317997}}, and {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=スサノオ}}.
== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichikama Onsen|qq=|1=Shichikama Onsen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11353724}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In [[:en:1868|1868]] (the first year of the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]]), it was renamed to its current title. In [[:en:1873|1873]] (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined [[:en:Hachiman|Hachiman]] and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Placenta deity|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
The shrine's main hall was rebuilt in [[:en:1444|1444]] (Bun'an 1, [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]]), but was destroyed in [[:en:1944|1944]] (Shōwa 19) due to a typhoon. The current structure was rebuilt after World War II.
== Festivals and Events == * Annual Festival: September 29<ref>{{Cite web|title=Festival Calendar - Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.kirinnomachi-japan-heritage.jp/jp/reisai/1059/|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs}}</ref>
