'''Sangu Shrine''' (山宮神社, *Sangu Jinja*) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located at Shichikama, Shin'onsen, Mikata District, [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]]. It was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|1=Son-sha|qid=Q134917284}}{{efn|Former shrine rank|lt=Son-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village shrine|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}}. The main deity enshrined is {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=オオヤマツミ}}, with additional enshrinements of [[:en:Izanagi|Izanagi]], [[:en:Izanami|Izanami]], {{ill|Homuda Wake no Mikoto|ja|誉田別尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Homuda Wake no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=応神天皇|1=Ōjin|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q317997}}, and {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=スサノオ}}.
== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichikama Onsen|qq=|1=Shichikama Onsen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11353724}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In [[:en:1868|1868]] (the first year of the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]]), it was renamed to its current title. In [[:en:1873|1873]] (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined [[:en:Hachiman|Hachiman]] and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Placenta deity|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
The shrine's main hall was rebuilt in [[:en:1444|1444]] (Bun'an 1, [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]]), but was destroyed in [[:en:1944|1944]] (Shōwa 19) due to a typhoon. The current structure was rebuilt after World War II.
== Festivals and Events == * Annual Festival: September 29<ref>{{Cite web|title=Festival Calendar - Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.kirinnomachi-japan-heritage.jp/jp/reisai/1059/|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs}}</ref>
== Cultural Properties == * '''Shichikama {{ill|Kirin Shishi-mai|ja|麒麟獅子舞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kirin Shishi-mai|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=麒麟獅子|1=Qilin dance|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11677329}} Dance''' - Town-designated Intangible Folk Cultural Property (designated March 31, 1986)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Shichikama Kirin Shishi-mai|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=8ab359199e3f3c495d46db6ceb3791ec|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref> * '''Sangu Shrine Sacred Forest''' (山宮神社社叢) - Town-designated Natural Monument (designated March 31, 1986), featuring ancient [[:en:Castanopsis sieboldii|Castanopsis]] and [[:en:Chamaecyparis obtusa|Hinoki cypress]] trees, along with thick growths of {{ill|Camellia japonica|ja|ヤブツバキ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Camellia japonica|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=ツバキ|1=Camellia japonica|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q160121}} and [[:en:Cleyera japonica|Sakaki]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sacred Forest of Shichikama Sangu Shrine|url=https://www.town.shinonsen.hyogo.jp/page/?mode=detail&page_id=b500773414376fa6bd4970ec294860e2|access-date=2022-12-19|publisher=Shin'onsen Town}}</ref>
== Access == * [[:en:West Japan Railway Company|West Japan Railway Company]] (JR West) [[:en:San'in Main Line|San'in Main Line]]: From [[:en:Hamasaka Station|Hamasaka Station]], take the {{ill|Zentan Bus|ja|全但バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zentan Bus|qq=|1=Zentan Bus|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11389110}} bound for {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|ja|湯村温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|qq=|1=Yumura Onsen (Hyōgo)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11563591}}, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi" bus stop. 5-minute walk. * From Osaka or Kobe, take the Zentan Bus {{ill|Yumechiyo-go|ja|夢千代号|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yumechiyo-go|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=全但バス|1=Zentan Bus|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11389110}} to "Yumura Onsen," transfer to the bus for Hamasaka, and get off at "Shichikama Onsen-guchi." 5-minute walk.
