== Overview == The shrine is located atop a small forested hill near the source of the {{ill|Shichikama Onsen|ja|七釜温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichikama Onsen|qq=|1=Shichikama Onsen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11353724}}. The exact founding date is unknown. Before the modern era, it was known as '''Sangami Gongen''' (山神権現). In [[:en:1868|1868]] (the first year of the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]]), it was renamed to its current title. In [[:en:1873|1873]] (Meiji 6), it was designated a village shrine and enshrined [[:en:Hachiman|Hachiman]] and the local {{ill|Placenta deity|ja|胞衣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Placenta deity|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
The shrine's main hall was rebuilt in [[:en:1444|1444]] (Bun'an 1, [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]]), but was destroyed in [[:en:1944|1944]] (Shōwa 19) due to a typhoon. The current structure was rebuilt after World War II.
